00:08:14,840 --> 00:08:16,140
Yeah,go on,Abs.
好了 繼續 Abs

180
00:08:16,660 --> 00:08:18,000
Abby's got something.
Abby發現了些什麼

181
00:08:30,160 --> 00:08:31,250
Watch out!
看呀!

182
00:08:31,340 --> 00:08:33,870
It's Halloween at Coyote Ugly, Piper Perabo.
這是在Coyote Ugly(電影名 講述紐約最熱門的酒吧)的萬聖節前夕 Piper Perabo

183
00:08:33,930 --> 00:08:36,480
Oh,if you like that one, you're gonna love this.
噢 如果你喜歡那個 那麼你也會喜歡這個的

184
00:08:36,700 --> 00:08:38,840
It's a,uh,it's a Sciuto original.
這是Sciuto(Abby)原創的

185
00:08:38,910 --> 00:08:41,130
I like to call it "Bottoms Up.」
我喜歡叫它"底朝天"

186
00:08:43,140 --> 00:08:45,120
I had no idea you were a bartender,Abby.
我不知道你還做過酒吧招待 Abby

187
00:08:45,160 --> 00:08:47,470
Well,my Uncle Teddy used to own a bar on Canal Street,
我的叔叔Teddy以前在Canal街有間酒吧

188
00:08:47,520 --> 00:08:49,240
and I used to bartend there on the weekends.
我經常在週末在那當侍應

189
00:08:51,960 --> 00:08:53,820
The case,Abby?
案子 Abby?

190
00:08:54,730 --> 00:08:58,030
But,Gibbs,you haven't even seen my famous Fire Bomb.
但是 Gibbs 你還沒欣賞過 我著名的燃燒彈呢

191
00:09:01,430 --> 00:09:02,610
It can wait.
那不急

192
00:09:02,790 --> 00:09:06,160
So,uh,I tested the blood that was in Petty Officer Cove's house.
我檢測了在Cove軍士房子裡的血跡

193
00:09:06,250 --> 00:09:08,900
Most of it was his, but one sample did not match.
大部分是他的 但是有個樣本不吻合

194
00:09:08,960 --> 00:09:12,610
It could've been from a prior accident or an altercation at one of his parties.
可能是之前的某個派對上 發生的意外或者口角時留下的

195
00:09:12,700 --> 00:09:13,940
Or it could be the killer's.
也可能是兇手的

196
00:09:14,030 --> 00:09:15,770
I also ran...
我還查了...

197
00:09:16,260 --> 00:09:18,660
the prints from our mystery cocktails.
神秘的雞尾酒杯上的指紋

198
00:09:18,740 --> 00:09:22,120
One half of our drinking duo was definitely Petty Officer Cove.
這兩杯飲料上一半指紋是Cove士官的

199
00:09:22,210 --> 00:09:23,120
The other half?
另外一半呢?

200
00:09:23,180 --> 00:09:25,020
Well,it's a work in progress,Gibbs.
還在查 Gibbs

201
00:09:25,080 --> 00:09:27,070
Tell me you have more than this,Abby.
告訴我你不止查到這些 Abby

202
00:09:27,160 --> 00:09:28,700
Have I ever let you down?
我有讓你失望過嗎?

203
00:09:28,760 --> 00:09:30,090
Don't answer that.
別回答

204
00:09:30,510 --> 00:09:33,040
Um,I'm using my mass spectrometer to break down
我用質譜儀分解了

205
00:09:33,100 --> 00:09:36,340
the molecular structure of the cocktails in question.
可疑雞尾酒中的分子結構

206
00:09:36,420 --> 00:09:37,690
Guessing that's where all these come in.
我猜就是變成這些東西的吧

207
00:09:37,760 --> 00:09:39,080
Well,you guessed correctly.
猜測正確

208
00:09:39,180 --> 00:09:43,920
I think I've made over 100 delightful beverages trying to find...
我想我製成超過100種好喝的飲料 想要找出...

209
00:09:45,260 --> 00:09:46,730
<i>the match.
符合這種的</i>

210
00:09:47,030 --> 00:09:50,450
The weird thing is, this baby isn't in any bartending guide anywhere.
奇怪的是 這個寶貝任何 任何酒吧侍應指南中都找不到

211
00:09:50,520 --> 00:09:52,530
It's made out of Jagermeister...
它的配方是野格酒...

212
00:09:52,650 --> 00:09:57,480
Cherry soda,vanilla vodka, lemon juice and a splash of Tabasco.
櫻桃蘇打 香草味伏特加 檸檬汁 再加一滴塔巴斯哥辣醬油

213
00:09:58,470 --> 00:10:00,230
It's called a "Hairy Hangover.」
叫做"危險宿醉"

214
00:10:01,030 --> 00:10:03,920
And you came to know this how,McGee?
你怎麼會知道的 McGee?

215
00:10:05,410 --> 00:10:06,630
I created it.
我創造的

216
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:12,310
******
我們失蹤的士官是我下本書的角色

217
00:10:19,220 --> 00:10:22,010
Cameron Meyer is a good old boy from Northern Virginia.
Cameron Meyer是從南佛吉尼亞 一個很好的大男孩

218
00:10:22,070 --> 00:10:24,630
"He was born with not much, raised with even less."
"他出生的時候一貧如洗 成長過程中被賦予的更少得可憐"

219
00:10:24,710 --> 00:10:27,390
All he wants out of life is a good girl and a great truck.
他只渴望生命中有個好姑娘和輛好車

220
00:10:27,480 --> 00:10:29,230
"As of yesterday,he's halfway there."
"而在昨天 他已經成功一半了"

221
00:10:29,300 --> 00:10:32,480
He dropped his life savings on a blue Ford Ranger.」
"他用他一生的積蓄 買了輛藍色的福特越野車"

222
00:10:33,860 --> 00:10:34,840
That's it?
就這些?

223
00:10:34,930 --> 00:10:36,120
Tony,it's all here.
Tony 就這麼多了

224
00:10:36,130 --> 00:10:39,310
The fuzzy dice,the cinnamon rolls, red track jacket.
長毛絨骰子 肉桂卷 紅色的田徑夾克

225
00:10:39,350 --> 00:10:41,620
<i>Petty Officer Cove is Cameron Meyer.
Cove軍士就是Cameron Meyer.</i>

226
00:10:41,690 --> 00:10:43,850
Uh,but how is that possible,McGee?
但那怎麼可能呢 McGee?

227
00:10:48,730 --> 00:10:51,860
My writing isn't entirely fiction. Okay?
我寫的東西並不是完全虛構的 知道嗎?

228
00:10:51,910 --> 00:10:53,120
My stories are,
我的故事是虛構的

229
00:10:53,240 --> 00:10:56,280
but sometimes I base my characters on people I...
但有時人物的原型是那些...

230
00:10:56,330 --> 00:10:57,680
Work with.
一起工作的

231
00:10:57,880 --> 00:10:59,140
See.
看見的

232
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:00,370
People I see.
我看見的人

233
00:11:00,520 --> 00:11:02,580
You've seen Petty Officer Cove before?
你以前見過Cove士官?

234
00:11:02,620 --> 00:11:04,300
Every morning at my coffee shop.
每天早上在我喝咖啡的店裡

235
00:11:04,380 --> 00:11:06,640
But how come you didn't recognize his photograph?
但你怎麼會沒認出他的照片呢?

236
00:11:06,690 --> 00:11:08,020
He only uses the drive-through.
他只使用"得來速"服務

237
00:11:08,080 --> 00:11:11,730
To me,he's just the large coffee with a cinnamon roll guy in the blue pickup.
對我來說 他只是個坐在藍色車裡 買大杯咖啡和肉桂卷的人

238
00:11:11,780 --> 00:11:12,810
I never saw his face.
我從沒見過他長什麼樣

239
00:11:12,880 --> 00:11:13,940
Whoa,whoa,wait-wait a minute.
哇 哇 等 等一下

240
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:14,820
Back up.
倒回去

241
00:11:14,900 --> 00:11:17,320
Your coffee shop has a drive-through?
你喝咖啡的店有"得來速"窗口?

242
00:11:17,450 --> 00:11:19,560
That's...That's not important.
那...那不重要

243
00:11:19,610 --> 00:11:22,140
Just because you based your character on a person who is missing,
就因為你人物的原型失蹤了

244
00:11:22,190 --> 00:11:25,130
does not necessarily mean the two of them are related,McGee.
並不代表這兩者有聯繫啊 McGee

245
00:11:25,180 --> 00:11:26,060
Yeah,it does.
有聯繫

246
00:11:26,990 --> 00:11:28,550
You created the drink.
你創造了那款飲料

247
00:11:28,670 --> 00:11:30,080
Made it up about a month ago.
大約一個月前想出來的

248
00:11:30,160 --> 00:11:32,530
How did two glasses of it get from your head
其中的兩杯怎麼從你的腦袋瓜裡出來

249
00:11:32,620 --> 00:11:34,860
to inside Petty Officer Cove's house?
跑到Cove軍士的房子裡去的?

250
00:11:34,920 --> 00:11:36,120
Someone's read your book.
有人讀過你的書

251
00:11:36,180 --> 00:11:37,830
Your papers under lock and key?
你的文章有妥善保管吧?

252
00:11:40,130 --> 00:11:42,520
Well,I sent my publisher a copy a couple weeks ago,
我幾周前給我的發行人寄了個副本

253
00:11:42,560 --> 00:11:43,700
but,you know,I'm sure she...
但是 我肯定她...

254
00:11:43,760 --> 00:11:44,950
Address.
地址

255
00:11:51,510 --> 00:11:52,970
boss,there's more.
頭 還有些別的事

256
00:11:54,530 --> 00:11:56,730
<i>Uh,after Deep Six hit the stores,
在深顫上市之後</i>

257
00:11:56,860 --> 00:12:01,850
my publishing firm received a ton of e-mails addressed to Thom E. Gemcity.
我的出版公司收到了很多郵件 是寄給Thom E. Gemcity的

258
00:12:02,400 --> 00:12:03,730
Tons?
很多?

259
00:12:09,710 --> 00:12:13,280
Most of them are autograph requests or feedback on the novel,
大部分是要親筆簽名或者是對小說的反饋

260
00:12:13,350 --> 00:12:14,770
but in the last couple weeks,
但在最近幾周

261
00:12:14,920 --> 00:12:17,240
my publisher says that we've gotten some really weird letters,
我的發行人說收到些很奇怪的信

262
00:12:17,300 --> 00:12:18,750
borderline obsessive.
到了著魔的邊緣

263
00:12:19,020 --> 00:12:21,580
I didn't say anything because I assumed they were harmless.
我沒說什麼因為我覺得他們沒什麼危險

264
00:12:21,660 --> 00:12:23,050
DiNozzo,with me.
DiNozzo 跟我走

265
00:12:23,230 --> 00:12:24,480
McGee,you stay here with Ziva.
McGee 你跟Ziva呆在這

266
00:12:24,540 --> 00:12:25,950
Start going through your book.
把你的書細讀一遍

267
00:12:26,020 --> 00:12:27,360
What exactly am I looking for?
我到底要找什麼?

268
00:12:27,410 --> 00:12:28,730
Answers,McGee.
答案 McGee

269
00:12:33,830 --> 00:12:36,090
Miss Crawshaw will be with you shortly.
Crawshaw小姐很快就來見你們

270
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:39,860
Oh,you got to be kidding me.
這一定是在開玩笑吧

271
00:12:40,560 --> 00:12:42,870
Is there anything else I can get you while you wait?
你們等候時需要些什麼嗎?

272
00:12:42,980 --> 00:12:44,250
Yeah,a barf bag.
是的 嘔吐袋

273
00:12:44,340 --> 00:12:45,290
I'm sorry.
對不起

274
00:12:45,330 --> 00:12:51,780
Todd,black tea,lemon,crab salad,arugula.
Todd 紅茶 檸檬 蟹肉沙拉 芝麻菜

275
00:12:52,770 --> 00:12:54,450
You're Timothy's people.
你們是Timothy的同事

276
00:12:55,270 --> 00:12:57,650
A few weeks ago, he sent you a draft of his next book?
幾周前他寄給你他下本書的草稿?

277
00:12:58,060 --> 00:12:59,660
Partial. It wasn't finished yet.
部分的 還沒完成呢

278
00:12:59,730 --> 00:13:01,410
Yeah,it still isn't,is it?
是啊 還沒完成呢 對嗎?

279
00:13:01,890 --> 00:13:03,830
How many of your people here have read the book?
你們這裡多少人讀過這本書了?

280
00:13:03,930 --> 00:13:04,830
Zero.

281
00:13:05,250 --> 00:13:07,730
No one in my agency has access to advance material
我這裡沒人能讀到還未出版的原作

282
00:13:07,760 --> 00:13:09,830
without the writer's consent.
除非經過作者同意

283
00:13:10,380 --> 00:13:11,150
Except you.
除了你

284
00:13:15,120 --> 00:13:17,480
Writers are notoriously insecure.
作者們是非常不可靠的

285
00:13:17,540 --> 00:13:18,510
Soft,even.
甚至是軟弱

286
00:13:18,590 --> 00:13:21,760
Well,that doesn't sound like our little Timmy McGee now,does it?
聽上去不像是我們的小Timmy McGee 對吧?

287
00:13:21,820 --> 00:13:23,960
Whether they ask for it or not,
不管他們是不是要求

288
00:13:24,020 --> 00:13:27,790
I provide coddling,prodding,protection.
我提供周到的 監督型的保護

289
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:31,320
Anything it takes to keep those elusive muses singing.
想盡一切辦法讓那些難以捉摸的 "繆斯"歌唱(指保持靈感)

290
00:13:31,880 --> 00:13:32,520
Agent...?
請問貴姓...?

291
00:13:33,550 --> 00:13:34,500
Gibbs.
Gibbs

292
00:13:37,110 --> 00:13:38,490
<i>Here we go. Rock Hollow:
找到了 空谷</i>

293
00:13:39,270 --> 00:13:41,760
<i>The Continuing Adventures of L.J. Tibbs.
L.J. Tibbs的冒險新歷程</i>

294
00:13:42,200 --> 00:13:44,130
How is this connected with your investigation?
這和你們的調查怎麼會有關係呢?

295
00:13:44,190 --> 00:13:44,900
A person's missing.
一個人失蹤了

296
00:13:44,950 --> 00:13:47,400
We believe it's related to the contents of that book.
我們相信和這本書的內容有關

297
00:13:48,670 --> 00:13:51,130
Guess I just made myself your prime suspect.
我猜我剛把自己變成你們的頭號嫌疑犯

298
00:13:51,610 --> 00:13:52,570
Sounds about right.
言之有理

299
00:13:54,190 --> 00:13:56,950
I may be the only one in the firm who's read it, Agent Gibbs,
我應該是公司裡唯一一個 讀過小說的人 Gibbs探員

300
00:13:57,030 --> 00:14:00,160
but I can guarantee you I'm not the only one in the city.
但我跟你肯定 我不是這城裡唯一一個讀過的人

301
00:14:00,660 --> 00:14:04,070
McGee hasn't given the book to anyone else, Miss Crawshaw.
McGee沒有把書給其他人看過 Crawshaw小姐

302
00:14:04,390 --> 00:14:09,020
Obsessed fans always find a way to get material early.
瘋狂粉絲總是會找到捷足先登的方法

303
00:14:09,090 --> 00:14:11,500
They dig through trash,hack computers,
他們翻垃圾 當黑客

304
00:14:11,580 --> 00:14:13,570
anything short of writing it themselves.
所有上面寫有字的東西

305
00:14:13,660 --> 00:14:17,200
And believe me, Timothy has some of the craziest fans I've ever seen.
相信我 Timothy擁有些 我聞所未聞的瘋狂粉絲

306
00:14:17,530 --> 00:14:18,660
Yeah,we know about the letters.
對 我們知道信的事

307
00:14:18,730 --> 00:14:20,170
Yeah,there are three that stand out.
沒錯 三個粉絲站出來

308
00:14:20,230 --> 00:14:21,610
Todd,bring me those three...
Todd 給我把那三封...

309
00:14:21,660 --> 00:14:23,000
Gemcity letters?
Gemcity的信?

310
00:14:23,330 --> 00:14:24,670
No return addresses.
沒有回郵地址

311
00:14:24,740 --> 00:14:26,960
Each one's stranger than the last.
一封比一封奇怪

312
00:14:27,030 --> 00:14:30,760
I bet the psychopath you're looking for is somewhere in that envelope.
我肯定你一定可以在信的某處找到那個變態

313
00:14:30,840 --> 00:14:32,600
What makes you think we're looking for a psychopath?
你為什麼會覺得我們找的是個變態?

314
00:14:32,650 --> 00:14:34,640
Don't you read crime novels?
你們不看犯罪小說嗎?

315
00:14:35,660 --> 00:14:37,980
There are always psychopaths.
裡面總是有變態出沒

316
00:14:39,840 --> 00:14:43,460
"I am sending this letter to express my gratitude
"我在此表達我內心的感激"

317
00:14:43,560 --> 00:14:46,220
"for the literary gift you've given me.
"感謝你給我這份文學大禮"

318
00:14:46,280 --> 00:14:47,900
"The majesty of your writing
"你文字的精妙

319
00:14:47,930 --> 00:14:51,040
is far beyond anything this planet has ever seen."
前無古人後無來者"

320
00:14:51,090 --> 00:14:52,450
A rave review.
高度讚譽

321
00:14:52,520 --> 00:14:54,120
Rave,indeed,Jethro.
讚譽 的確 Jethro

322
00:14:54,170 --> 00:14:54,870
Yeah.
對

323
00:14:54,930 --> 00:14:56,630
In fact,it's quite possible that
看來 這個Michael很可能是

324
00:14:56,670 --> 00:15:00,160
Michael is Timothy's greatest admirer.
Timothy的頭號崇拜者

325
00:15:00,290 --> 00:15:02,440
Admirer,or stalker,Duck?
崇拜者 還是跟蹤狂 Duck?

326
00:15:02,700 --> 00:15:04,010
At this point,I'd say
從這點上 我要說

327
00:15:04,050 --> 00:15:07,420
<i>he is no immediate threat to himself or anyone else.
他尚不會對自己或者他人造成威脅</i>

328
00:15:07,470 --> 00:15:08,270
At this point?
從哪點?

329
00:15:08,330 --> 00:15:11,500
Well,one does not become a predatory stalker overnight,Jethro.
沒人會在一夜之間變成激進跟蹤狂的 Jethro

330
00:15:11,550 --> 00:15:14,590
The mind typically goes through three stages.
這種思想一般經歷三個階段

331
00:15:14,650 --> 00:15:16,390
This letter,strange as it may seem,
這封信 看上去古里古怪

332
00:15:16,430 --> 00:15:20,160
is only at stage one-- the attraction stage.
僅僅是第一階段--情有獨鍾

333
00:15:20,210 --> 00:15:21,060
And the other two?
那剩下兩個呢?

334
00:15:21,100 --> 00:15:23,180
Well,on the surface,
從表面來看

335
00:15:23,210 --> 00:15:26,090
this letter,written by Andrew,
這封信 作者是Andrew

336
00:15:26,140 --> 00:15:27,700
would appear more normal,
看上去正常些

337
00:15:27,780 --> 00:15:30,600
but phrases like "I breathe for your words"
但卻使用了"我呼吸著你的文字"

338
00:15:30,640 --> 00:15:32,220
and "you need me,"
還有"你需要我"等句子

339
00:15:32,300 --> 00:15:33,120
might suggest...
極可能顯示...

340
00:15:33,170 --> 00:15:34,230
Otherwise.
事實相反

341
00:15:35,650 --> 00:15:38,240
Yeah,because of that sense of desperation,
對 因為這種極度絕望的語氣

342
00:15:38,470 --> 00:15:42,880
I categorized that letter as stage two-- obsession.
我把這封信歸為第二階段--陷入瘋狂

343
00:15:42,980 --> 00:15:44,290
What's stage three?
第三階段是什麼?

344
00:15:44,390 --> 00:15:46,560
Well,read for yourself.
你自己讀讀看

345
00:15:49,710 --> 00:15:52,620
"I know you think of me often, just as I think of you.
