386
00:17:47,780 --> 00:17:49,430
Not the way I choose to write,Tony.
那不是我選擇的寫作方式 Tony

387
00:17:49,500 --> 00:17:52,150
And he wonders why he has writer's block.
而且他想知道為什麼他也有瓶頸

388
00:17:52,200 --> 00:17:54,010
Can we focus on the problem here?
我們能把精力放在眼前的問題上嗎?

389
00:17:54,070 --> 00:17:57,330
We've got a missing person and our only lead is my book.
有人失蹤了 唯一線索就是我的書

390
00:17:57,370 --> 00:17:58,940
Well,that's not much of a lead.
這可算不上什麼唯一線索

391
00:17:59,020 --> 00:18:01,430
She's right. We don't even know how the book factors in.
她說得沒錯 我們甚至不知道書的因素有多大

392
00:18:01,500 --> 00:18:02,420
We do now.
現在知道了

393
00:18:02,920 --> 00:18:04,970
The letters were written by the same person.
三封信都是同一個人寫的

394
00:18:05,190 --> 00:18:06,680
He thinks the book is real.
他認為書裡的描寫是真實的

395
00:18:07,210 --> 00:18:10,350
And believes Petty Officer Cove is a part of it.
還相信士官Cove就是其中的一部分

396
00:18:10,430 --> 00:18:14,230
