意思是我們要去所有他去過的地方

397
00:18:14,320 --> 00:18:15,390
Well,we've already done that,though.
呃 我們已經去過了

398
00:18:15,450 --> 00:18:17,710
His home,work,hangout spots.
他的家 工作地點 休閒場所

399
00:18:17,790 --> 00:18:20,070
I'm not talking about Petty Officer Cove.
我不是說士官Cove

400
00:18:20,130 --> 00:18:22,350
I'm talking about your good old boy--
我是指你的老相好

401
00:18:22,550 --> 00:18:24,430
with the pickup truck.
開小型貨車那個

402
00:18:24,790 --> 00:18:26,300
Cameron Meyer.
Cameron Meyer

403
00:18:26,480 --> 00:18:29,100
High Side Creek, where Cameron goes to clear his head.
高邊灣 Cameron經常來這裡清理思路

404
00:18:30,110 --> 00:18:32,630
Thematically, this location is very important,boss.
從主題上來說 這個地點非常重要 頭

405
00:18:32,710 --> 00:18:34,510
You've been saying the same thing all morning,McGee.
你整個早上都在說這件事 McGee

406
00:18:34,580 --> 00:18:35,580
Spread out.
分頭搜索

407
00:18:35,650 --> 00:18:38,330
Why would Cameron come to a picnic area to think?
為什麼Cameron在一個 人家野餐的地方思考?

408
00:18:38,390 --> 00:18:40,330
In his book,it's not a picnic area.
在他書裡 這裡不是野餐用的

409
00:18:40,400 --> 00:18:41,460
It's his favorite fishing hole.
他最喜歡來這裡釣魚

410
00:18:41,510 --> 00:18:42,400
Thank you,Ziva.
謝謝 Ziva

411
00:18:42,460 --> 00:18:44,320
Don't you think it's kind of a clich?
你不覺得這有點老套嗎?

412
00:18:44,370 --> 00:18:46,830
to have your character alone,
讓你的角色獨處

413
00:18:46,860 --> 00:18:49,190
staring into the serene wilderness?
望著寂靜的大自然發呆?

414
00:18:49,230 --> 00:18:52,060
No. If it was, I wouldn't have written it,Tony.
不 如果老套 我是不會這麼寫的 Tony

415
00:18:52,090 --> 00:18:54,460
I mean,knowing Cameron, if he was bummed out,
我說 瞭解了Cameron 如果他不高興

416
00:18:54,490 --> 00:18:56,460
wouldn't he just go to the Wing Shack with his buddies,
他就不能跟老友們去Wing Shack酒吧

417
00:18:56,490 --> 00:18:58,600
and toss back a few brews?
喝幾杯小酒?

418
00:18:58,670 --> 00:19:00,080
Or talk to a priest?
或者去跟神父傾訴?

419
00:19:00,160 --> 00:19:03,260
Don't forget that he's very religious, now that his father died.
別忘了他可是個虔誠的教徒 現在他父親又死了

420
00:19:03,320 --> 00:19:04,150
Good point.
說得好

421
00:19:04,180 --> 00:19:05,750
No,it isn't.
不 不是這樣的

422
00:19:06,070 --> 00:19:08,440
Cameron keeps his emotions bottled up.
Cameron是個壓抑情緒的人

423
00:19:08,660 --> 00:19:10,500
When he's upset,he comes here.
當他難過時 他就來這

424
00:19:10,550 --> 00:19:12,390
Afterwards,he always feels better.
然後 他心情就會好轉

425
00:19:12,830 --> 00:19:14,310
Not always.
不一定

426
00:19:26,740 --> 00:19:27,880
That's him.
是他

427
00:19:28,930 --> 00:19:30,330
That's Petty Officer Cove.
這是士官Cove

428
00:19:31,770 --> 00:19:33,280
Then who is this?!
那這是誰?

429
00:19:43,600 --> 00:19:45,040
That's Jared Brenner.
這是Jared Brenner

430
00:19:47,360 --> 00:19:49,210
That's another character from my book.
我書裡的另外一個角色

431
00:19:57,080 --> 00:19:58,310
Two bodies,
兩具屍體

432
00:19:58,650 --> 00:20:03,110
