Yeah,it's like cuckoo mail.
對 就像鴨尾酒郵件

580
00:25:59,530 --> 00:26:01,020
No,no,no,I just made it up.
不不不 我剛編的

581
00:26:01,060 --> 00:26:02,560
Um,nothing on the truck.
呃 車上什麼都沒有

582
00:26:02,610 --> 00:26:05,040
All the latent prints belong to Petty Officer Cove.
所有的指紋都是士官Cove的

583
00:26:05,100 --> 00:26:07,910
But on the c-mail, there's dozens of different prints.
但是在鴨郵件有十幾個不同的指紋

584
00:26:07,950 --> 00:26:09,920
Well,that makes sense 'cause paper mail gets processed
那就說得通了 因為郵件會經過很多流程

585
00:26:09,960 --> 00:26:12,420
through post offices, delivery trucks,mailrooms.
郵局 郵車 收發室

586
00:26:12,460 --> 00:26:13,420
Exactly.
沒錯

587
00:26:14,240 --> 00:26:19,000
There's still one spot that only the sender touches.
但有一個地方是只有寄信人會觸摸到的

588
00:26:19,380 --> 00:26:20,790
The back of the stamp.
郵票的背面

589
00:26:20,900 --> 00:26:22,060
You pulled a print?
你提取指紋了?

590
00:26:22,470 --> 00:26:25,590
Not only did I pull a print, I already got a match.
不僅僅提取了 還找到了符合對像

591
00:26:32,020 --> 00:26:32,920
Todd Ryder,
Todd Ryder

592
00:26:33,060 --> 00:26:35,610
arrested last year for possession of marijuana.
去年因為私藏大麻被逮捕

593
00:27:03,860 --> 00:27:05,570
Looking for something,Timothy?
在找什麼 Timothy

594
00:27:09,450 --> 00:27:10,760
I'm just looking.
我只是看看

595
00:27:12,310 --> 00:27:13,830
Petty Officer Cove... ....
士官Cove...

596
00:27:15,000 --> 00:27:16,610
wasn't just a partier.
並不是一個花天酒地的人

597
00:27:16,660 --> 00:27:18,820
I called his elderly parents.
我給他的父母打了電話

598
00:27:18,930 --> 00:27:21,570
Visited em every day for two hours.
每天花兩小時去看他們

599
00:27:23,180 --> 00:27:27,180
This guy,Adrian Corbett,
這人名叫Adrian Corbett

600
00:27:28,120 --> 00:27:29,870
he just got married.
新婚不久

601
00:27:31,300 --> 00:27:34,890
Yes,I took off his wedding ring.
是的 我摘下了他的婚戒

602
00:27:36,600 --> 00:27:39,780
Not quite the notorious playboy I made him out to be,huh?
跟我塑造的臭名昭著的 花花公子形象相去甚遠吧？

603
00:27:39,940 --> 00:27:42,200
Appearances can be deceptive.
不能以貌取人

604
00:27:42,330 --> 00:27:44,900
Every single word I wrote was wrong.
我寫下的每個字都鑄成了錯

605
00:27:44,970 --> 00:27:47,930
No,every word you wrote was fiction.
不 你的字字句句都是在虛構小說

606
00:27:48,280 --> 00:27:50,410
That's why they call them "characters.」
所以他們稱之為"角色"

607
00:27:50,500 --> 00:27:52,370
But they're not just characters in a book.
但在書裡他們不僅僅是角色

608
00:27:53,350 --> 00:27:54,870
They're real people...
他們有血有肉...

609
00:27:55,630 --> 00:27:57,280
and real families.
有真正的家庭

610
00:27:59,480 --> 00:28:00,780
Were.
曾經如此

611
00:28:04,770 --> 00:28:08,950
I sympathize with the way you feel, Timothy......
我明白你有多難受 Timothy...

612
00:28:13,600 --> 00:28:16,850
but you are not to blame for any of this.
但這一切都不能怪你

613
00:28:19,390 --> 00:28:20,790
Tell them that.
跟他們說去吧

614
00:28:28,930 --> 00:28:29,950
Todd!
Todd!

615
00:28:32,150 --> 00:28:33,170
Oh,God.
哦 我的天

616
00:28:34,930 --> 00:28:36,010
Look out!
小心!

617
00:28:36,160 --> 00:28:37,180
What do you call that?
你把那叫成什麼?

618
00:28:37,430 --> 00:28:38,710
Running,I think.
我想是 跑

619
00:28:42,710 --> 00:28:43,600
Todd!
Todd!

620
00:28:43,690 --> 00:28:44,510
嗨!
嗨!

621
00:28:45,840 --> 00:28:47,100
Where's his car?
他的車在哪兒?

622
00:28:48,160 --> 00:28:49,600
Where's his car?!
他的車在哪兒?!

623
00:28:49,720 --> 00:28:51,410
Employee lot around back.
後面的員工車位

624
00:28:52,560 --> 00:28:53,970
Get out of the building!
快離開大樓!

625
00:28:54,050 --> 00:28:55,040
They know!
他們知道了!

626
00:28:55,180 --> 00:28:56,490
They're chasing me!
他們在追趕我!

627
00:29:00,460 --> 00:29:02,190
You should've left the top down.
你真該把敞篷打開

628
00:29:03,470 --> 00:29:05,080
Put your hands on top of your head.
把手舉過頭頂

629
00:29:07,290 --> 00:29:09,410
Nice of you to join us,DiNozzo.
你能加入我們真是太好了 DiNozzo

630
00:29:10,540 --> 00:29:12,470
thought I was gaining ground.
以為我要佔上風了呢

631
00:29:12,720 --> 00:29:14,830
He got a very unorthodox running style.
他的跑步風格很另類

632
00:29:14,940 --> 00:29:16,550
It's very effective,though.
但非常有效

633
00:29:16,810 --> 00:29:18,170
Not effective enough.
還不夠有效

634
00:29:18,970 --> 00:29:20,440
I didn't want to do it.
我不想這麼做

635
00:29:20,650 --> 00:29:22,550
I told her it was a bad idea.
我跟她說了這是個餿主意

636
00:29:31,170 --> 00:29:32,610
I actually trusted her.
我真的信任過她

637
00:29:32,710 --> 00:29:34,610
There was no way you could have known,McGee.
你不可能知道的 McGee

638
00:29:34,680 --> 00:29:37,280
Ziva's right,probie, it's not your fault.
Ziva說得對 菜鳥 這不能怪你

639
00:29:37,770 --> 00:29:40,930
But if you even think about writing a third novel,I'll kill you.
但如果你還想寫第三部小說 我會殺了你

640
00:29:41,130 --> 00:29:44,350
When Abby finds out who her character really fell in love with,
如果Abby查明她的角色跟誰傾心相愛

641
00:29:44,440 --> 00:29:46,190
you will already be dead.
你也必死無疑

642
00:29:50,100 --> 00:29:53,530
I have been sitting here half the night,Agent Gibbs.
我在這兒坐了半個晚上了 Gibbs探員

643
00:29:53,980 --> 00:29:55,490
What am I being charged with?
我被指控犯了什麼罪?

644
00:29:55,550 --> 00:29:57,610
Tampering with a federal investigation.
妨礙聯邦調查

645
00:29:57,910 --> 00:29:58,610
That'sidiculous.
荒謬

646
00:29:58,620 --> 00:30:00,040
I've answered every question you've asked.
所有問題我都一五一十回答了

647
00:30:00,120 --> 00:30:01,470
Resisting arrest.
拒捕

